      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Competitive contest. WOOTTON WAY (2) Wootton Bassett filly ready to win third-up in a weaker contest. Stalked the speed in the heavy (8) conditions with a sound third over 1100m at Warwick Farm. On the quick back-up and expected to go close. TENNESSEE DOLLY (8) comfortable Maiden winner first-up at Goulburn, then slow into stride and struck trouble shortly after before warming up late to finish fourth over 1100m at Hawkesbury. Likely to go back from the draw and be ridden for luck. Each-way. SHE SWINGS (3) progressive mare who looks set for a big campaign. Went quickly through the grades last time in when fourth to Oui Oui Oui over 1400m at Randwick in BM72 grade. Fitted with the two trials and can finish over the top of these. KORITSI (9) ploughed through the heavy going at start nine to shed her Maiden tag over 1262m at Taree. Maps well again and don't dismiss.",
